 Following a day of rains, the Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality on Thursday said that its Disaster Management and Traffic Management Directorates were out monitoring the situation while urging drivers to drive with caution. "Officials at municipal community centres have been told to prepare the venues for accommodating people affected by flooding, should that occur," described Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality Spokesperson, Mthubanzi Mniki. "Drivers are advised to drive with caution, watch their following distance." 